WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:40.248 --> 00:00:43.043 position:50% align:center
Ah! How are we
this morning, Zen?

00:00:43.126 --> 00:00:47.630 position:50% align:center
Guess who got
overzealous making dinner?

00:00:47.714 --> 00:00:49.424 position:50% align:center
Care for some stew?

00:00:52.552 --> 00:00:55.096 position:50% align:center
You're always so kind to me.

00:00:56.306 --> 00:01:00.268 position:50% align:center
[sighs] So many crows
around here these days.

00:01:00.352 --> 00:01:02.479 position:50% align:center
Makes putting out
the trash a nightmare.

00:01:02.562 --> 00:01:06.316 position:50% align:center
Time was there used to be
enough cats to ward them off.

00:01:06.399 --> 00:01:08.401 position:50% align:center
Oh yeah, speaking of.

00:01:08.485 --> 00:01:10.278 position:50% align:center
I heard it's happening again.

00:01:10.362 --> 00:01:12.989 position:50% align:center
Seems someone went after
another stray in the park.

00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:16.701 position:50% align:center
[CROWS cawing]

00:01:21.039 --> 00:01:23.458 position:50% align:center
[NEIGHBOR 10A yelps]

00:01:29.297 --> 00:01:32.384 position:50% align:center
[grunts] What was that about?

00:01:32.467 --> 00:01:35.136 position:50% align:center
[ZEN] Thank you for
the leftovers, ma'am.

00:01:35.220 --> 00:01:37.639 position:50% align:center
I'll wash the container
before giving it back.

00:01:37.722 --> 00:01:39.182 position:50% align:center
[NEIGHBOR 10A]
Uh!

00:01:39.265 --> 00:01:41.643 position:50% align:center
Gracious!

00:01:41.726 --> 00:01:45.397 position:50% align:center
You've got blood on your hand.
Is everything okay?

00:01:45.480 --> 00:01:47.148 position:50% align:center
[ZEN sighs]

00:01:50.068 --> 00:01:53.154 position:50% align:center
Just an issue with broken glass.

00:01:54.906 --> 00:01:56.491 position:50% align:center
[door slams]

00:04:27.976 --> 00:04:29.853 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 10A]
I'm done...

00:04:31.396 --> 00:04:33.565 position:50% align:center
Please tell me it's
close to lunchtime.

00:04:33.648 --> 00:04:35.358 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] We're barely
through second period.

00:04:35.442 --> 00:04:37.986 position:50% align:center
I know, but by the
time I finished breakfast,

00:04:38.069 --> 00:04:41.114 position:50% align:center
it was too late to eat
before I took off for school.

00:04:41.197 --> 00:04:43.700 position:50% align:center
You mean you were
too busy eating to eat.

00:04:43.783 --> 00:04:45.201 position:50% align:center
Hey, Miko.

00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:48.663 position:50% align:center
I'm starting to get worried.

00:04:48.747 --> 00:04:51.708 position:50% align:center
I dunno. Just feels like
I'm hungry all the time.

00:04:51.791 --> 00:04:52.667 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Shocking.

00:04:52.751 --> 00:04:56.004 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Hey! I'm being serious!

00:04:56.087 --> 00:04:58.423 position:50% align:center
You being a bottomless
pit is nothing new.

00:04:58.506 --> 00:05:00.300 position:50% align:center
I have an overactive metabolism!

00:05:00.383 --> 00:05:02.177 position:50% align:center
Your snark is uncalled for!

00:05:02.260 --> 00:05:03.928 position:50% align:center
Sorry, I'll dial it back.

00:05:04.012 --> 00:05:05.138 position:50% align:center
[HANA whines]
Jeez.

00:05:05.221 --> 00:05:07.140 position:50% align:center
It's really
bothering me, you know!

00:05:07.223 --> 00:05:09.225 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
You'll be fine.

00:05:13.813 --> 00:05:15.899 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Besides,

00:05:15.982 --> 00:05:18.234 position:50% align:center
it might just be
a blessing in disguise.

00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:19.527 position:50% align:center
There's the love!

00:05:19.611 --> 00:05:20.403 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Simmer down.

00:05:20.487 --> 00:05:21.237 position:50% align:center
[whistle sounds]

00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:22.781 position:50% align:center
Ah!

00:05:22.864 --> 00:05:24.574 position:50% align:center
One more lap!

00:05:24.657 --> 00:05:26.242 position:50% align:center
Let's move those legs!

00:05:26.326 --> 00:05:28.661 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 10C]
Thanks, I hate it.

00:05:28.745 --> 00:05:30.330 position:50% align:center
Okay then, let's race!

00:05:30.413 --> 00:05:34.042 position:50% align:center
Uhh! But I don't wanna!

00:05:34.125 --> 00:05:37.337 position:50% align:center
[HANA yells] Why you
gotta run like a gazelle?

00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:41.299 position:50% align:center
Some of us are already working
with a calorie deficit! [cries]

00:05:41.383 --> 00:05:44.094 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Hmph. This is actually
making me feel better.

00:05:44.177 --> 00:05:45.720 position:50% align:center
--[footsteps]
--Uh?

00:05:45.804 --> 00:05:49.933 position:50% align:center
Too slow!

00:05:50.016 --> 00:05:53.395 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:05:55.188 --> 00:05:57.941 position:50% align:center
[RUNNING MONSTER 10A hums]

00:06:01.236 --> 00:06:04.364 position:50% align:center
What's the deal? I thought
we were racing; are we done?

00:06:04.447 --> 00:06:05.657 position:50% align:center
Yeah, we're done.

00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:08.076 position:50% align:center
I vote we go at your
pace the rest of the way.

00:06:08.159 --> 00:06:09.744 position:50% align:center
Um.

00:06:09.828 --> 00:06:12.205 position:50% align:center
I'm trying to figure out
if that was a dig.

00:06:12.288 --> 00:06:14.582 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Sorry. Blame my mood.

00:06:16.835 --> 00:06:19.462 position:50% align:center
[MORINO] "As rumor had said,
he found several corpses

00:06:19.546 --> 00:06:21.673 position:50% align:center
strewn carelessly
about the floor.

00:06:21.756 --> 00:06:23.883 position:50% align:center
Since the glow of
the light was feeble,

00:06:23.967 --> 00:06:25.635 position:50% align:center
he could not count the number.

00:06:25.719 --> 00:06:29.472 position:50% align:center
He could only see that some
were naked and others clothed.

00:06:29.556 --> 00:06:31.141 position:50% align:center
Some of them were women,

00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:33.184 position:50% align:center
and all were lolling
on the floor

00:06:33.268 --> 00:06:35.895 position:50% align:center
with their mouths open
or their arms outstretched,

00:06:35.979 --> 00:06:38.898 position:50% align:center
showing no more signs of life
than so many clay dolls."

00:06:38.982 --> 00:06:41.359 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Very good. Thank you, Yamada.

00:06:41.443 --> 00:06:43.611 position:50% align:center
I keep telling you, it's Morino!

00:06:43.695 --> 00:06:46.114 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI] How many times
are you gonna mess that up?

00:06:46.197 --> 00:06:48.283 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
That's right. Sorry, Morino.

00:06:48.366 --> 00:06:51.119 position:50% align:center
C'mon, it can't be that hard
to keep track of our names.

00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.955 position:50% align:center
Not going senile, are you?

00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:56.332 position:50% align:center
[ZEN groans]

00:06:57.375 --> 00:06:59.169 position:50% align:center
I feel bad for you, Chie.

00:06:59.252 --> 00:07:02.380 position:50% align:center
Your taste in guys is
gonna be your downfall.

00:07:02.464 --> 00:07:03.923 position:50% align:center
Oh, keep it to yourself.

00:07:04.007 --> 00:07:05.842 position:50% align:center
He'll remember it next time.

00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:08.011 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI]
What do you see in him?

00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:09.012 position:50% align:center
He's hot.

00:07:09.095 --> 00:07:10.597 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI]
In what way?

00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:13.141 position:50% align:center
In that "mysterious loner with
a tragic history" kinda way...

00:07:13.224 --> 00:07:15.435 position:50% align:center
Don't look at him.

00:07:15.518 --> 00:07:16.644 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI]
Seriously?

00:07:16.728 --> 00:07:18.355 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
Completely serious.

00:07:18.438 --> 00:07:19.481 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI]
You're so messed up.

00:07:19.564 --> 00:07:21.649 position:50% align:center
Pardon me. Suzuki, please?

00:07:21.733 --> 00:07:23.651 position:50% align:center
[HASEGAWA] There's no Suzuki in
this class!

00:07:23.735 --> 00:07:24.861 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS laugh]

00:07:24.944 --> 00:07:26.696 position:50% align:center
Imagine him whispering
all his dark secrets

00:07:26.780 --> 00:07:29.157 position:50% align:center
in your ear and tell me
that doesn't do it for you.

00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:31.993 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I recognize this one.

00:07:32.077 --> 00:07:33.370 position:50% align:center
[inaudible]

00:07:33.453 --> 00:07:36.289 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I've seen it before.

00:07:36.373 --> 00:07:39.167 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Okay, next reader.

00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:40.418 position:50% align:center
Ogawa, please.

00:07:40.502 --> 00:07:44.214 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
Hey, no cheat sheets!

00:07:44.297 --> 00:07:46.299 position:50% align:center
"Only their shoulders,
breasts, and torsos

00:07:46.383 --> 00:07:47.467 position:50% align:center
stood out in the dim light,

00:07:47.550 --> 00:07:51.429 position:50% align:center
all other features
vanished in shadow." Ew.

00:07:51.513 --> 00:07:54.557 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Doesn't seem
to realize I can see it.

00:07:54.641 --> 00:07:58.561 position:50% align:center
As long as I don't look
at the teacher, I'm golden.

00:07:58.645 --> 00:07:59.437 position:50% align:center
Except...

00:07:59.521 --> 00:08:05.527 position:50% align:center
[CAT MONSTERS yowling]

00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:15.036 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Now it's a party.

00:08:17.831 --> 00:08:22.961 position:50% align:center
[WINDOW MONSTER 09A screeching]

00:08:25.338 --> 00:08:27.632 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Okay, then. That's new.

00:08:27.716 --> 00:08:30.969 position:50% align:center
Wait. I've seen this before.

00:08:31.052 --> 00:08:33.805 position:50% align:center
On the train the other day.

00:08:33.888 --> 00:08:37.017 position:50% align:center
Should I go to the
axe monster for help?

00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:38.685 position:50% align:center
No. What am I thinking?

00:08:38.768 --> 00:08:40.520 position:50% align:center
That's a terrible idea.

00:08:40.603 --> 00:08:42.480 position:50% align:center
I'm not even sure how
to communicate with it.

00:08:42.564 --> 00:08:43.565 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Next, Yotsuya.

00:08:43.648 --> 00:08:44.899 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
For all I know its trauma

00:08:44.983 --> 00:08:45.984 position:50% align:center
could be way worse than--

00:08:46.067 --> 00:08:47.986 position:50% align:center
--[ZEN] Miko Yotsuya?
--[MIKO gasps]

00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:49.487 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Yes?

00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:51.489 position:50% align:center
Your turn. Please continue.

00:08:51.573 --> 00:08:53.742 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:08:53.825 --> 00:08:58.705 position:50% align:center
[WINDOW MONSTER 09A groans]

00:09:03.001 --> 00:09:05.628 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasping]

00:09:15.972 --> 00:09:17.766 position:50% align:center
Don't you look at him.

00:09:17.849 --> 00:09:22.270 position:50% align:center
"I-It seemed to be an old woman

00:09:22.354 --> 00:09:24.272 position:50% align:center
with a pine torch
in her right hand."

00:09:24.356 --> 00:09:28.485 position:50% align:center
Don't you dare look at him!

00:09:28.568 --> 00:09:30.862 position:50% align:center
"She was peeping..."

00:09:30.945 --> 00:09:33.073 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Oh, no. Don't cry.

00:09:33.156 --> 00:09:34.115 position:50% align:center
Not now!

00:09:34.199 --> 00:09:36.910 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
"She was peeping into

00:09:36.993 --> 00:09:40.747 position:50% align:center
the face of a corpse
with long, black hair."

00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:42.332 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Keep it together.

00:09:42.415 --> 00:09:44.376 position:50% align:center
Don't let it know
you can see it!

00:09:44.459 --> 00:09:48.463 position:50% align:center
"More out of horror
than out of curiosity,

00:09:48.546 --> 00:09:51.132 position:50% align:center
he even forgot to breathe."

00:09:51.216 --> 00:09:51.966 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Hey.

00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:53.760 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:10:04.479 --> 00:10:06.189 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Oh, no!

00:10:06.272 --> 00:10:07.107 position:50% align:center
Is there something--

00:10:07.190 --> 00:10:09.567 position:50% align:center
[stomach rumbling]

00:10:09.651 --> 00:10:11.152 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Huh?

00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:13.071 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Hm?

00:10:13.154 --> 00:10:15.448 position:50% align:center
I'm so sorry. I just...

00:10:15.532 --> 00:10:18.993 position:50% align:center
...don't think I can keep
doing this on an empty stomach.

00:10:19.077 --> 00:10:22.122 position:50% align:center
Can I go rest in
the nurse's office?

00:10:25.333 --> 00:10:29.004 position:50% align:center
[WINDOW MONSTER 09A groans]

00:10:29.087 --> 00:10:31.464 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:10:31.548 --> 00:10:33.341 position:50% align:center
Hana's hungry again!

00:10:33.425 --> 00:10:34.843 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI]
We need bread, stat!

00:10:34.926 --> 00:10:37.012 position:50% align:center
Careful on the way!
Don't starve!

00:10:37.095 --> 00:10:40.140 position:50% align:center
Leave her alone.
She's got a high metabolism.

00:10:43.601 --> 00:10:45.395 position:50% align:center
I'll make sure
she gets there okay!

00:10:45.478 --> 00:10:48.565 position:50% align:center
[HANA grunts]

00:10:48.648 --> 00:10:49.816 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 10E]
Look at Miko!

00:10:49.899 --> 00:10:52.861 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 10F]
Aw, being the Good Samaritan!

00:11:03.538 --> 00:11:05.582 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
I'm really sorry about this.

00:11:05.665 --> 00:11:08.376 position:50% align:center
I don't know what's
going on with me today.

00:11:08.460 --> 00:11:10.128 position:50% align:center
Right at the beginning
of third period,

00:11:10.211 --> 00:11:12.714 position:50% align:center
I got super hungry
all of sudden.

00:11:12.797 --> 00:11:13.715 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Hana...

00:11:13.798 --> 00:11:16.092 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:11:16.176 --> 00:11:17.886 position:50% align:center
You're the best ever.

00:11:17.969 --> 00:11:19.763 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I'm saved!

00:11:19.846 --> 00:11:22.474 position:50% align:center
Wait... You think I'm gonna die?

00:11:22.557 --> 00:11:24.017 position:50% align:center
'Course not.

00:11:25.060 --> 00:11:26.770 position:50% align:center
As the disease progressed,

00:11:26.853 --> 00:11:29.898 position:50% align:center
the swollen lymph nodes
would hemorrhage and necrotize,

00:11:29.981 --> 00:11:32.192 position:50% align:center
causing the tissue to darken.

00:11:32.275 --> 00:11:34.569 position:50% align:center
The plague came to be
known as the Black Death.

00:11:34.652 --> 00:11:36.905 position:50% align:center
The majority of those
infected would perish,

00:11:36.988 --> 00:11:39.407 position:50% align:center
with over 25 million dead--

00:11:51.628 --> 00:11:53.505 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
Excuse me.

00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:55.632 position:50% align:center
Hi there! Something wrong?

00:11:55.715 --> 00:11:56.841 position:50% align:center
Do you not feel well?

00:11:56.925 --> 00:11:58.259 position:50% align:center
[door sliding]

00:11:58.343 --> 00:12:04.015 position:50% align:center
It's not that. I was--
Did a girl come in here?

00:12:04.099 --> 00:12:05.558 position:50% align:center
[KIDO]
Oh, of course!

00:12:05.642 --> 00:12:07.560 position:50% align:center
Back there.

00:12:07.644 --> 00:12:10.188 position:50% align:center
Your friend is all right.

00:12:10.271 --> 00:12:12.023 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
My friend?

00:12:15.735 --> 00:12:17.112 position:50% align:center
--[MIKO grunts]
--[HANA gasps]

00:12:17.195 --> 00:12:18.905 position:50% align:center
Hi, Yulia!

00:12:18.988 --> 00:12:22.617 position:50% align:center
I looked up and saw you
two walking down the hall.

00:12:22.701 --> 00:12:25.537 position:50% align:center
I'm glad you came
to check up on me!

00:12:25.620 --> 00:12:28.373 position:50% align:center
So, what's up? Everything okay?

00:12:28.456 --> 00:12:31.501 position:50% align:center
Mostly. Not everything.

00:12:31.584 --> 00:12:34.212 position:50% align:center
She's fine other
than being hungry.

00:12:34.295 --> 00:12:35.714 position:50% align:center
Seriously?

00:12:35.797 --> 00:12:37.257 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
It's my fault.

00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:39.968 position:50% align:center
This is what happens
when you skip meals.

00:12:40.051 --> 00:12:41.761 position:50% align:center
When have you done that?

00:12:41.845 --> 00:12:44.472 position:50% align:center
I didn't have second
breakfast today.

00:12:45.974 --> 00:12:50.353 position:50% align:center
Okay. I'd never heard of that,
but I guess these might help.

00:12:50.437 --> 00:12:52.147 position:50% align:center
Mushroom candies.

00:12:53.565 --> 00:12:55.567 position:50% align:center
[HANA grunts]

00:12:58.069 --> 00:13:01.573 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Mm! Mm... Mm.

00:13:01.656 --> 00:13:04.826 position:50% align:center
[HANA moans]

00:13:04.909 --> 00:13:07.454 position:50% align:center
Thank you! I feel alive!

00:13:07.537 --> 00:13:09.789 position:50% align:center
[YULIA] Were you
really starving that badly?

00:13:09.873 --> 00:13:11.416 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
I can't believe I had to go

00:13:11.499 --> 00:13:15.378 position:50% align:center
to the nurse's office for being
hungry. Isn't that wild?

00:13:15.462 --> 00:13:19.841 position:50% align:center
Betcha Mr. Zen is gonna think
I lost all of my chickens.

00:13:19.924 --> 00:13:22.719 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
Oh, right, the new substitute.

00:13:22.802 --> 00:13:24.929 position:50% align:center
I think he might be the problem.

00:13:25.013 --> 00:13:26.514 position:50% align:center
Being around him
and those spirits

00:13:26.598 --> 00:13:29.476 position:50% align:center
would be a drain on
anyone's life aura.

00:13:29.559 --> 00:13:31.478 position:50% align:center
Wait, what's a life aura?

00:13:31.561 --> 00:13:32.937 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
Hm?

00:13:33.021 --> 00:13:34.397 position:50% align:center
[YULIA grunts]

00:13:41.279 --> 00:13:42.280 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:42.364 --> 00:13:45.492 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
I forgot Hana isn't in on this!

00:13:45.575 --> 00:13:46.534 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
I mean, uh,

00:13:46.618 --> 00:13:48.161 position:50% align:center
he's always such
a downer, you know?

00:13:48.244 --> 00:13:51.581 position:50% align:center
A body burns a lot of calories
around someone like that.

00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:54.042 position:50% align:center
Well, that candy
sure pepped me up!

00:13:54.125 --> 00:13:56.127 position:50% align:center
[YULIA chuckles]

00:13:56.211 --> 00:13:58.546 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:13:58.630 --> 00:13:59.631 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
Oh, crap.

00:13:59.714 --> 00:14:03.093 position:50% align:center
That's definitely a death glare.

00:14:03.176 --> 00:14:05.512 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Can Yulia see that thing, too?

00:14:05.595 --> 00:14:08.682 position:50% align:center
No, from the way
she was talking,

00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:12.644 position:50% align:center
I don't think she can sense the
giant one following him around.

00:14:13.895 --> 00:14:17.232 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Either way, what did
she say about Hana's aura?

00:14:17.315 --> 00:14:19.734 position:50% align:center
It's getting drained?

00:14:19.818 --> 00:14:22.570 position:50% align:center
Those things must be
drawn to her because of it.

00:14:22.654 --> 00:14:26.032 position:50% align:center
Is there a connection
to why she's so hungry?

00:14:26.116 --> 00:14:29.536 position:50% align:center
If he's the reason Hana got so
much worse all of a sudden...

00:14:34.249 --> 00:14:35.875 position:50% align:center
[YULIA stammers]
Well, anyway...

00:14:35.959 --> 00:14:37.752 position:50% align:center
It's good to know you're okay!

00:14:37.836 --> 00:14:38.795 position:50% align:center
[YULA chuckles]

00:14:38.878 --> 00:14:40.088 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Hmm...

00:14:40.171 --> 00:14:42.007 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
Now she's super mad!

00:14:42.090 --> 00:14:45.135 position:50% align:center
I thought I was off the hook!

00:14:45.218 --> 00:14:47.637 position:50% align:center
Oh, gosh. That's a scary face.

00:14:47.721 --> 00:14:49.097 position:50% align:center
Huh? Oh, I'm sorry.

00:14:49.180 --> 00:14:51.558 position:50% align:center
[YULIA whimpers]

00:14:51.641 --> 00:14:53.309 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Maybe she could
tell me about the stuff

00:14:53.393 --> 00:14:55.270 position:50% align:center
I don't know yet.

00:14:55.353 --> 00:14:58.273 position:50% align:center
Yulia, do you have a second?

00:14:58.356 --> 00:14:59.774 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:59.858 --> 00:15:01.192 position:50% align:center
Oh.

00:15:02.193 --> 00:15:04.362 position:50% align:center
[inaudible]

00:15:04.446 --> 00:15:07.198 position:50% align:center
Um! Sorry.

00:15:07.282 --> 00:15:10.285 position:50% align:center
I, uh... I could be late!

00:15:10.368 --> 00:15:11.995 position:50% align:center
[door slams]

00:15:17.709 --> 00:15:19.210 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:15:22.172 --> 00:15:23.548 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Huh?

00:15:36.394 --> 00:15:37.312 position:50% align:center
Here's yours!

00:15:37.395 --> 00:15:41.232 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Ooh! This looks so good!

00:15:42.275 --> 00:15:44.736 position:50% align:center
You had a gigantic
lunch, didn't you?

00:15:44.819 --> 00:15:47.113 position:50% align:center
That was forever ago, though.

00:15:48.615 --> 00:15:51.159 position:50% align:center
[HANA cries]

00:15:51.242 --> 00:15:54.245 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] I couldn't find
Yulia after school, either.

00:15:54.329 --> 00:15:55.497 position:50% align:center
You want some of this?

00:15:55.580 --> 00:15:57.874 position:50% align:center
No, thank you.
What is it, anyway?

00:15:57.957 --> 00:15:59.250 position:50% align:center
I don't even know!

00:15:59.334 --> 00:16:01.002 position:50% align:center
[PEOPLE chattering]

00:16:01.086 --> 00:16:06.257 position:50% align:center
[HANA sighs]
It's so chill here.

00:16:06.341 --> 00:16:08.802 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Hm.

00:16:08.885 --> 00:16:11.971 position:50% align:center
[PARK MONSTER 10A groans]

00:16:12.055 --> 00:16:16.768 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] When I look around,
they really are everywhere.

00:16:16.851 --> 00:16:19.521 position:50% align:center
That one's gonna
nest inside a guy.

00:16:19.604 --> 00:16:22.232 position:50% align:center
[HANA sighs]
It's so peaceful!

00:16:22.315 --> 00:16:24.567 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I really shouldn't look.

00:16:24.651 --> 00:16:27.487 position:50% align:center
I can't see life auras or
anything like that, but.

00:16:27.570 --> 00:16:30.198 position:50% align:center
This has an awesome mouthfeel!

00:16:30.281 --> 00:16:33.326 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] I do know Hana
has always eaten a lot.

00:16:33.410 --> 00:16:36.329 position:50% align:center
I've only started seeing
things recently, though.

00:16:36.413 --> 00:16:39.541 position:50% align:center
Maybe this has been
going on for a while.

00:16:39.624 --> 00:16:41.001 position:50% align:center
Either way,

00:16:41.084 --> 00:16:44.170 position:50% align:center
for some reason, it's been
getting a lot worse lately.

00:16:45.630 --> 00:16:48.383 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] I thought this would
all go away if I ignored it.

00:16:48.466 --> 00:16:50.760 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:16:50.844 --> 00:16:53.054 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Clearly the wrong tac.

00:16:54.556 --> 00:16:56.850 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Ah! Bye-bye!

00:16:56.933 --> 00:16:58.018 position:50% align:center
[GIRL 10A]
Bye-bye!

00:16:58.101 --> 00:17:01.062 position:50% align:center
Oh my gosh, kids are
so cute, can't they?

00:17:01.146 --> 00:17:02.063 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:17:02.147 --> 00:17:03.898 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:17:03.982 --> 00:17:05.734 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:17:08.236 --> 00:17:09.070 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Hey, Miko?

00:17:09.154 --> 00:17:10.530 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:12.490 --> 00:17:14.534 position:50% align:center
You seem kinda blue today.

00:17:14.617 --> 00:17:16.411 position:50% align:center
You doin' all right?

00:17:16.494 --> 00:17:18.038 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:19.873 --> 00:17:21.249 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Hm?

00:17:23.168 --> 00:17:24.419 position:50% align:center
[MIKO chuckles]

00:17:24.502 --> 00:17:27.213 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Well, I don't
need you worrying about me.

00:17:27.297 --> 00:17:29.924 position:50% align:center
Which one of us
needed to lie down?

00:17:30.008 --> 00:17:32.844 position:50% align:center
[HANA] Ugh. Could you not
blow me off for once, please?

00:17:32.927 --> 00:17:37.265 position:50% align:center
I know, sorry. Thank you, but
I'm gonna be okay. I promise.

00:17:45.398 --> 00:17:47.734 position:50% align:center
Kids really are adorable.

00:17:51.529 --> 00:17:52.614 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:52.697 --> 00:17:54.199 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 10A]
Hello?

00:17:54.282 --> 00:17:57.035 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A grunts]

00:17:57.118 --> 00:17:58.203 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:58.286 --> 00:17:59.537 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A]
You saw me.

00:17:59.621 --> 00:18:03.500 position:50% align:center
You saw me.
I know you saw me.

00:18:03.583 --> 00:18:05.669 position:50% align:center
[MIKO whimpers]

00:18:05.752 --> 00:18:08.797 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A] You can see
me. I know that you can see me.

00:18:08.880 --> 00:18:11.007 position:50% align:center
Can't you? [yells]

00:18:11.091 --> 00:18:12.509 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:18:16.054 --> 00:18:19.015 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A shrieks]

00:18:30.610 --> 00:18:33.113 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A groans]

00:18:34.739 --> 00:18:36.157 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A shouts]

00:18:39.202 --> 00:18:40.829 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A chuckles]

00:18:41.830 --> 00:18:43.123 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:18:44.582 --> 00:18:48.795 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A cackling]

00:18:52.465 --> 00:18:54.175 position:50% align:center
[BOY MONSTER 10A chuckles]

00:18:58.513 --> 00:19:00.015 position:50% align:center
[MIKO whimpers]

00:19:01.099 --> 00:19:03.101 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Mm, mm!

00:19:16.781 --> 00:19:18.742 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:19:18.825 --> 00:19:21.036 position:50% align:center
[FOX SPIRIT 06A whispers]

00:19:25.999 --> 00:19:28.084 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:19:28.168 --> 00:19:30.295 position:50% align:center
[PEOPLE chattering]

00:19:30.378 --> 00:19:31.921 position:50% align:center
[CHILD 10A]
Wait up, guys!

00:19:32.005 --> 00:19:33.506 position:50% align:center
[CHILD 10A laughs]

00:19:33.590 --> 00:19:36.801 position:50% align:center
[HANA] They're always
so sweet and innocent!

00:19:39.763 --> 00:19:43.224 position:50% align:center
Three times...

00:19:43.308 --> 00:19:44.559 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Wait, did that mean...?

00:19:44.642 --> 00:19:46.353 position:50% align:center
[heart pounds]

00:19:56.404 --> 00:19:59.115 position:50% align:center
[FOX SPIRIT 06A whispers]

00:20:02.118 --> 00:20:04.913 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
It'll help me three times?

00:20:04.996 --> 00:20:07.707 position:50% align:center
It'll protect me from the
dangerous ones,

00:20:07.791 --> 00:20:09.793 position:50% align:center
and that was number two.

00:20:09.876 --> 00:20:11.461 position:50% align:center
Which means...

00:20:12.671 --> 00:20:16.132 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
...the next one is the last one.

00:20:16.216 --> 00:20:18.802 position:50% align:center
[stomach rumbles]

00:20:18.885 --> 00:20:22.389 position:50% align:center
Really? But I just
ate a few minutes ago!

00:22:10.246 --> 00:22:13.500 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
The flavor is next level. Mm!

00:22:13.583 --> 00:22:16.044 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI]
For real. So good.

00:22:16.127 --> 00:22:18.004 position:50% align:center
What the heck is
in this thing, anyway?

00:22:18.088 --> 00:22:21.883 position:50% align:center
I don't even know, and to be
honest, I don't really care.

00:22:29.432 --> 00:22:30.725 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:22:38.483 --> 00:22:40.735 position:50% align:center
Okay... Weird.

00:22:41.861 --> 00:22:44.989 position:50% align:center
[CAT 10A squeaking]

00:22:45.073 --> 00:22:49.411 position:50% align:center
[footsteps]

00:22:49.494 --> 00:22:51.121 position:50% align:center
[CAT 10A meows]

00:23:00.088 --> 00:23:04.801 position:50% align:center
[CAT 10A growls]

00:23:04.884 --> 00:23:07.387 position:50% align:center
[CAT 10A hissing]

00:23:07.470 --> 00:23:10.181 position:50% align:center
[yowls]

00:23:11.474 --> 00:23:13.643 position:50% align:center
